                "logprobs": [],
                "text": "On that page, the **“Sources”** section explains that:\n\n- You can use the **`sources` field** to see **all URLs** retrieved during a web search.  \n- This is different from **inline citations**, which show only the **most relevant** references; `sources` returns the **complete list of URLs** the model consulted, so there are often **more sources than citations**.  \n- It also includes **real-time third‑party feeds**, which are labeled as `oai-sports`, `oai-weather`, or `oai-finance`.  \n- The `sources` field is available for both the **`web_search`** and **`web_search_preview`** tools. ([developers.openai.com](https://developers.openai.com/api/docs/guides/tools-web-search))"
              }
